I didn't wanna be
interviewed anymore.

20:48.673 --> 20:51.089
I don't want
to talk to anybody else

20:51.172 --> 20:54.381
about the McDonald's thing.

20:54.464 --> 20:56.506
'Cause it was...

20:56.589 --> 20:58.547
a whole lot.

21:00.589 --> 21:03.547
I was a McDonald's
$1 million winner.

21:04.714 --> 21:07.923
And...this is the first time

21:08.005 --> 21:10.631
that I've really just
had the opportunity to just--

21:10.714 --> 21:13.214
to just really just say,
"Okay, I'm gonna lay all

21:13.297 --> 21:15.381
my cards on the table
and to tell everything."

21:15.464 --> 21:17.798
I mean...I mean--even though

21:17.881 --> 21:20.589
my sister was there,
she don't know all the details.

21:20.673 --> 21:22.756
I mean, she'll be hearing this

21:22.839 --> 21:25.673
for the first time herself,
some of this stuff.

21:29.464 --> 21:34.297
I have a son, and I raised
him as a single parent.

21:34.381 --> 21:36.756
He, as a child,
was very understanding.

21:36.839 --> 21:40.464
We had a relationship where,
if money was not available,

21:40.547 --> 21:44.756
I'd discuss it with him,
and we worked it out together.

21:45.673 --> 21:47.756
I always had to work,
and I always managed

21:47.839 --> 21:51.214
to keep a job,
but it was always a struggle.

21:52.214 --> 21:55.005
Years passed by
and I didn't see Robin

21:55.089 --> 21:57.714
for some years and, um,

21:57.798 --> 21:59.547
when she called me,

21:59.631 --> 22:01.547
she told me
she had got married.

22:01.631 --> 22:04.130
I'm thinking maybe now
she has somebody that can

22:04.214 --> 22:08.047
look out for her and she was
very happy being with Jerry.

22:10.089 --> 22:12.130
I think it was in '97.

22:12.214 --> 22:14.130
Robin had called me and said

22:14.214 --> 22:16.339
she had something
she wanted to discuss with me,

22:16.422 --> 22:18.255
but we couldn't talk
about it over the phone.

22:19.172 --> 22:22.005
So Jerry asked me
to come and visit.

22:22.089 --> 22:25.089
It was at their home
in South Carolina.

22:26.089 --> 22:28.464
My first impression
of Jerry Colombo was that

22:28.547 --> 22:31.673
he was a real-life
comedian type guy, you know.

22:31.756 --> 22:34.005
And he treated me

22:34.089 --> 22:36.172
just like I had been around
the whole time.

22:36.255 --> 22:40.339
But the thing that bothered me
is that there was never

22:40.422 --> 22:43.172
any time that she and I
could be alone,

22:43.255 --> 22:46.547
even when we went shopping,
he went shopping with us.

22:46.631 --> 22:48.381
[laughing]

22:48.464 --> 22:49.964
One night I had just said,

22:50.047 --> 22:52.506
"Can you just leave us alone
for a few minutes?

22:52.589 --> 22:54.089
Durn, Jerry."

22:54.172 --> 22:55.506
And then he left us alone

22:55.589 --> 22:57.297
just for a few minutes,
and he came back.

22:57.381 --> 23:00.464
We were not allowed
to really discuss anything.

23:04.547 --> 23:07.422
Finally he talked to me
about a proposition,

23:07.506 --> 23:11.798
and it was a proposition
that would help me.

23:11.881 --> 23:13.714
He asked me, was I familiar

23:13.798 --> 23:15.589
with the McDonald's
game piece?

23:15.673 --> 23:17.047
I said yes.

23:17.130 --> 23:18.381
So he said

23:18.464 --> 23:22.339
people are picked
to be winners.

23:22.422 --> 23:24.673
This is how
it's always been done.

23:24.756 --> 23:27.839
And then he told me that

23:27.923 --> 23:31.673
he would let me know
what the next step was.

23:34.422 --> 23:37.172
When I first got the offer...

23:38.339 --> 23:40.381
I thought to myself

23:40.464 --> 23:43.339
that it was a blessing
that came knocking at my door.

23:46.714 --> 23:48.089
And...

23:48.172 --> 23:49.714
you know, I was going to church

23:49.798 --> 23:54.047
and I was doing--trying
to do the right thing and...

23:54.130 --> 23:58.547
my son was young,
and I was making...

23:59.673 --> 24:04.339
Probably about $24,000 a year,
it was just...

24:05.756 --> 24:07.673
By the time
taxes and stuff come out,

24:07.756 --> 24:09.506
it's really nothing.

24:09.589 --> 24:12.214
And I just
wanted a better life,

24:12.297 --> 24:14.631
and I just felt like
this was my opportunity.

24:14.714 --> 24:16.964
And I said, "Well,

24:17.047 --> 24:20.214
this couldn't come to me
if it wasn't meant for me."

24:24.881 --> 24:26.923
- My brother was
always joking around,

24:27.005 --> 24:29.089
always making people laugh,
always having a good time.

24:29.172 --> 24:33.756
Very lighthearted, uh,
but if you pissed him off,

24:33.839 --> 24:35.964
then he can have
a temper as well.

24:36.047 --> 24:38.839
But he never was the type
of person who would grab you

24:38.923 --> 24:40.464
or, you know, threaten you...
- Or rough you up.

24:40.547 --> 24:41.631
- Or rough you up.

24:41.714 --> 24:43.464
You knew if he looked at you

24:43.547 --> 24:46.506
when he told you exactly
what he wanted you to do,

24:46.589 --> 24:48.506
you knew you had to do it.

24:52.923 --> 24:55.881
- The whole
relationship changed.

24:57.255 --> 25:00.464
It got to the point that
I didn't talk to Robin anymore,

25:00.547 --> 25:03.297
I only talked
to Jerry Colombo.

25:03.381 --> 25:08.172
And I finally got
the information from him

25:08.255 --> 25:11.673
that I was gonna be
a $1 million winner

25:11.756 --> 25:14.381
and that he needed me
to come up with some money.

25:14.464 --> 25:17.255
And I'm asking him, "Why?"

25:17.339 --> 25:19.422
Then he said,
"Everybody that wins

25:19.506 --> 25:22.339
has to give
some upfront money."

25:22.422 --> 25:24.923
And I'm like, "How much?"

25:25.714 --> 25:28.005
And he asked me
how much I could come up with?

25:28.089 --> 25:30.631
I said, "I really
don't have any money,"

25:30.714 --> 25:34.255
so he said, "Can you get
money off your house?"

25:34.339 --> 25:37.297
[dramatic music]

25:37.381 --> 25:44.089
♪ ♪

25:44.172 --> 25:47.214
Can't back out now.
He's told me too much.

25:48.589 --> 25:54.172
I mortgaged my home
to get my upfront money.

25:54.255 --> 26:01.339
♪ ♪

26:06.297 --> 26:09.839
I put all the stuff
I worked hard for on the line

26:09.923 --> 26:14.839
because I believed
that this was my blessing.

26:20.464 --> 26:23.631
I met him
on the side of the road

26:23.714 --> 26:26.547
and gave him my first
portion of my money.

26:26.631 --> 26:33.839
♪ ♪

26:38.297 --> 26:41.881
It felt like something
had just been ripped from me.

26:41.964 --> 26:43.798
And, you know,
to meet somebody

26:43.881 --> 26:49.297
on the side of the road
and give them cash money,

26:49.381 --> 26:52.172
that much at one time...

26:53.214 --> 26:55.005
that's more than I ever
had in my hand at one time

26:55.089 --> 26:57.798
in my life, and I just
had to give it all away.

26:58.839 --> 27:02.381
I just felt that
I just had gave my life away

27:02.464 --> 27:06.005
and I'm giving it to somebody
I don't know much about.

27:06.089 --> 27:08.923
Can I even trust this guy?
You know.

27:09.005 --> 27:16.214
