32:52.547 --> 32:54.964
I'm going to the FBI," I said,

32:55.047 --> 32:57.381
"I'm going to the Witness
Protection Program,"

32:57.464 --> 33:00.506
I said, "so just watch out."

33:05.005 --> 33:07.839
So I go to a payphone;
I called my parents.

33:07.923 --> 33:11.756
And I said, "Mom, I need you
to take two names down."

33:11.839 --> 33:13.923
She goes,
"What the hell have you done?"

33:14.005 --> 33:16.381
I said, "Well I just
threatened three goons

33:16.464 --> 33:21.130
"with the FBI, so if you don't
hear from me in a couple days,

33:21.214 --> 33:24.214
you are to contact them
and give them these names."

33:24.297 --> 33:26.673
And Uncle Jerry was
the top of that--

33:26.756 --> 33:29.381
on that...list.

33:30.089 --> 33:31.381
They beat me home.

33:31.464 --> 33:34.255
My husband
and two big-ass goons.

33:35.923 --> 33:37.839
And I said,
"This is what I want.

33:37.923 --> 33:42.130
I want a moving truck here
and a divorce."

33:44.839 --> 33:47.464
He goes, "Robin,
you're never leaving me.

33:47.547 --> 33:49.297
"There is no divorce.

33:49.381 --> 33:51.297
You're stuck with me."

33:52.255 --> 33:55.172
So I called Uncle Jerry,
and he says,

33:55.255 --> 33:57.381
"You married the wrong guy,"

33:57.464 --> 34:00.422
and he asked me to marry him.

34:01.673 --> 34:02.923
Yeah.

34:05.130 --> 34:06.756
- Yeah.

34:06.839 --> 34:09.172
And I told him no.

34:09.255 --> 34:12.881
I thought, you know, "I'm
never gonna get out of this,"

34:12.964 --> 34:15.089
so I stayed.

34:15.172 --> 34:17.839
But I was a prisoner
in my own home.

34:36.005 --> 34:38.464
- Jerry Colombo told me
that I had to have

34:38.547 --> 34:40.381
a South Carolina address.

34:40.464 --> 34:44.631
And he had a cousin that lived
at this particular spot,

34:44.714 --> 34:47.172
and this was gonna
be my address.

34:48.130 --> 34:49.964
And at that point,
I'm like,

34:50.047 --> 34:51.673
"Oh, gosh."

34:52.673 --> 34:55.339
This isn't what
I was expecting.

34:57.005 --> 35:00.756
He coached me on some things
that I needed to say

35:00.839 --> 35:03.631
and work on and believe...

35:03.714 --> 35:08.047
I had to leave my voice on the
voicemail as if it was my home.

35:08.130 --> 35:09.756
Hi, this is Gloria.

35:09.839 --> 35:12.631
Leave a message,
and I'll get back with you.

35:12.714 --> 35:15.547
He made me do it
till I got it right.

35:15.631 --> 35:18.005
You know, he wanted
the right tone, you know.

35:18.089 --> 35:19.589
It had to be happy.

35:20.714 --> 35:24.214
One of the things that
constantly crossed my mind

35:24.297 --> 35:28.422
is that my life was in danger.

35:28.506 --> 35:32.631
I had no other option but
to take this process through.

35:34.839 --> 35:37.464
Robin knew all of my family

35:37.547 --> 35:40.381
and my son.

35:41.381 --> 35:43.714
I just kind of felt
like I was trapped.

35:44.923 --> 35:47.589
It was no way out,
but to go through it.

35:48.381 --> 35:50.255
When time to
turn the game piece in,

35:50.339 --> 35:52.798
he picked me up with two men.

35:52.881 --> 35:54.798
I didn't know
either one of them.

35:54.881 --> 35:56.714
I almost felt
kidnapped in a sense,

35:56.798 --> 35:58.673
you know what I'm saying?
It's like,

35:58.756 --> 36:00.547
"You're here, and
you're gonna ride with us

36:00.631 --> 36:02.422
and you're gonna do
what we say."

36:03.881 --> 36:05.506
"And you're gonna do it right."

36:07.464 --> 36:08.798
All the way there,

36:08.881 --> 36:10.297
Jerry Colombo
never stopped talking.

36:10.381 --> 36:11.589
Telling me what to do

36:11.673 --> 36:12.798
and what you're gonna say.

36:12.881 --> 36:13.964
I mean, he was just drilling--

36:14.047 --> 36:16.005
and how you're gonna do it.

36:16.089 --> 36:18.464
And they drove me
to the McDonald's

36:18.547 --> 36:21.881
that they had picked out
that I was gonna go to.

36:21.964 --> 36:25.506
He parked the car
in the corner.

36:25.589 --> 36:29.130
The ticket was in a little vial
about this tall

36:29.214 --> 36:31.547
with a cap on it.

36:32.923 --> 36:35.339
There I was,
walking down this block

36:35.422 --> 36:37.673
in a place
I had never been before.

36:37.756 --> 36:40.005
It was like bank robbery
or something, you know?

36:40.089 --> 36:41.255
They on the block
down at the end.

36:41.339 --> 36:42.506
They don't wanna be seen.

36:42.589 --> 36:44.798
They down the street,
the getaway car.

36:44.881 --> 36:48.756
And I'm like, "Oh, Lord,
this could go so bad."

36:50.547 --> 36:53.089
A lot of things was
going through my mind.

36:54.255 --> 36:58.047
Am I gonna lie
enough to be believable?

36:58.130 --> 37:01.089
Am I gonna mess up
and then I'm in trouble?

37:01.172 --> 37:04.631
Just all kind of stuff
was going through my head.

37:04.714 --> 37:08.130
Am I going to jail today
behind this foolishness?

37:09.047 --> 37:11.381
And at this point in time,

37:11.464 --> 37:14.255
I was about to panic.

37:14.339 --> 37:16.589
And I'm saying to myself...

37:16.673 --> 37:18.964
"Oh, Lord, Jesus."

37:19.047 --> 37:21.756
I wanted to cry before
I got into the place

37:21.839 --> 37:25.130
and I said, "No,
you can't go in there upset."

37:26.339 --> 37:28.631
I had to not
be Gloria at that time,

37:28.714 --> 37:33.506
I had to become somebody else
to make it believable.

37:39.964 --> 37:42.547
Here we go.

37:45.172 --> 37:47.798
I had to go in
and stand to this counter

37:47.881 --> 37:52.047
and tell them that it looked
like I'd been a winner.

37:53.589 --> 37:56.381
The manager came out said,
"Have a seat."

37:56.464 --> 37:59.297
And I had to give them
my information--

37:59.381 --> 38:03.673
the fake telephone number,
the fake address.

38:03.756 --> 38:06.714
[dramatic music]

38:06.798 --> 38:13.881
♪ ♪

38:45.798 --> 38:48.881
And then they finally came out
and congratulated me.

38:48.964 --> 38:52.089
The manager at the McDonald's,
the cashiers,

38:52.172 --> 38:54.297
everybody running around
so happy

38:54.381 --> 38:58.589
that they got the winner
come to their McDonald's.

38:59.464 --> 39:01.130
And there I was,
I couldn't even hardly

39:01.214 --> 39:02.964
put a smile on my face.

39:07.589 --> 39:10.172
By the time I got to the car--
got back to the car,

39:10.255 --> 39:12.464
Jerry Colombo
was having a fit.

39:13.714 --> 39:16.422
Because it had take--
it took too long.

39:17.798 --> 39:20.673
And there he was,
as soon as I get in the car,

39:20.756 --> 39:22.547
"Okay, what took you so long?"

39:22.631 --> 39:24.339
Then I had to explain to him.

39:24.422 --> 39:26.631
"Well what were you doing
all that time?"

39:26.714 --> 39:28.964
"I was sitting waiting,"
you know.

39:29.673 --> 39:31.214
"What did they tell you?"

39:31.297 --> 39:35.089
So they told me they'd get
back--be getting back with me.

39:36.839 --> 39:38.339
I hung around another day

39:38.422 --> 39:41.130
and then I came on back
to Jacksonville.

39:42.089 --> 39:44.089
And went back to work

39:44.172 --> 39:47.172
like nothing had happened
and I just had to wait.

39:51.506 --> 39:53.381
- They don't want to see
this club open up.

39:53.464 --> 39:55.172
- And anybody in the
Ladson-Summerville area

39:55.255 --> 39:57.047
knows that place has been
a bar for 50 years.

39:57.130 --> 39:59.422
It's been a bikers' club.
It's been a nightclub.

39:59.506 --> 40:00.964
It's been a lounge.

40:01.047 --> 40:02.881
- My brother would use

40:02.964 --> 40:04.839
loopholes after
loophole after loophole,

40:04.923 --> 40:06.964
and they finally came up
with one that was saying,

40:07.047 --> 40:10.130
uh, you can't have
female dancers within

40:10.214 --> 40:11.798
1,000 feet of a school
or something--

40:11.881 --> 40:13.714
something to that nature,
what it was.

40:13.798 --> 40:17.047
So he turned the Fuzzy Bunny

40:17.130 --> 40:19.089
into the Church of Fuzzy Bunny.

40:19.172 --> 40:20.547
- The Church
of Fuzzy Bunny's

40:20.631 --> 40:21.881
- The Church of Fuzzy Bunny's.

40:21.964 --> 40:23.297
- The transformation
of their club

40:23.381 --> 40:24.589
into a church...

40:24.673 --> 40:26.923
- Dancing girls,
alcoholic drinks,

40:27.005 --> 40:28.089
and the Bible?

40:28.172 --> 40:29.464
Lowcountry Preachers

40:29.547 --> 40:32.506
say the switch from
Fuzzy Bunny Club

40:32.589 --> 40:34.089
to Fuzzy Bunny Church

40:34.172 --> 40:36.464
is nothing but blasphemy.

40:36.547 --> 40:38.047
- I really, honestly,
didn't see the big deal in it,

40:38.130 --> 40:39.756
I'll be honest with you.
100%, I swear.

40:39.839 --> 40:41.756
And I mean, I'm a woman,
but I--I really

40:41.839 --> 40:43.714
didn't see the--
the huge deal.

40:43.798 --> 40:46.214
- Those two don't mix,
as far as I'm concerned.

40:46.297 --> 40:49.506
Church and strip joints
just don't mix.

40:49.589 --> 40:51.089
- Yeah, but they
can't fool people.

40:51.172 --> 40:52.839
No good people is gonna
be going in that place.

40:52.923 --> 40:54.506
- I don't see nothing
with having a place

40:54.589 --> 40:56.130
where you can come in,
say a few prayers,

40:56.214 --> 40:59.422
have a couple drinks,
see some women dancing.

40:59.506 --> 41:01.506
- He liked to be
the center of attention,

41:01.589 --> 41:03.172
uh, and if you
messed with him,

41:03.255 --> 41:05.798
he would just play
that game as long as it took.

41:05.881 --> 41:07.297
- Marianne,
you're next on the line

41:07.381 --> 41:08.714
with Jerry Colombo, go ahead.

41:08.798 --> 41:10.130
Go ahead, Marianne.

41:10.214 --> 41:12.214
- Yes, um, I think
what you're doing

41:12.297 --> 41:14.422
is an abomination to God.

41:15.422 --> 41:18.130
And it's wrong,
it's wrong in the eyes of God.

41:18.214 --> 41:20.255
And really, it's wrong
in morals, too.

41:20.339 --> 41:21.339
- All right.

41:21.422 --> 41:22.714
- Thank you.

41:22.798 --> 41:24.130
- Well, I guess God
hasn't talked to you lately.

41:24.214 --> 41:25.673
He came to me in
a dream a couple weeks ago,

41:25.756 --> 41:27.923
and he told me what
I'm doing is fine.

41:28.005 --> 41:30.631
- You say that with somewhat
of a smirk on your face,

41:30.714 --> 41:32.130
I mean, you had to have...

41:32.214 --> 41:34.130
- I did have--I did have
a dream one night, that's why.

41:34.214 --> 41:35.589
- Well, we all have dreams,

41:35.673 --> 41:37.005
I don't know if
it's divine intervention.

41:37.089 --> 41:38.964
- This one was divine.

41:39.047 --> 41:40.339
- We never went.
- No.

41:40.422 --> 41:42.798
- No--but it sounded
like a fun time, though.

41:42.881 --> 41:46.297
- I mean, a little prayer,
a little pasties...

41:46.381 --> 41:48.089
- Right?
[laughter]

41:48.172 --> 41:50.547
- All the publicity that has
come out of this situation

41:50.631 --> 41:53.381
with Fuzzy Bunny's has earned
owner, Jerry Colombo,

41:53.464 --> 41:56.005
notice from
"The National Enquirer,"

41:56.089 --> 41:58.130
Comedy Central,
the cable channel,

41:58.214 --> 42:00.964
and this Friday, he has
a scheduled guest appearance

42:01.047 --> 42:03.381
on the David Letterman show.

42:11.255 --> 42:13.547
- Oh, yeah.
Yes.

42:14.255 --> 42:16.172
- Jerry Colombo
won a Dodge Viper.

42:16.255 --> 42:18.130
- Jerry Colombo...
- Jerry Colombo...

42:18.214 --> 42:19.589
- Jerry Colombo...

42:19.673 --> 42:21.506
- Jerry Colombo...
- Jerry Colombo...

42:21.589 --> 42:24.506
[dramatic music]

42:24.589 --> 42:31.381
♪ ♪

42:31.464 --> 42:35.506
- This is my first
letter of congratulation.

42:35.589 --> 42:39.172
They're congratulating me
for being a $1 million winner

42:39.255 --> 42:42.964
and explaining to me that
I'll be getting $50,000

42:43.047 --> 42:47.172
for, um, the next 20 years.

42:49.756 --> 42:51.339
The check came in the mail,

42:51.422 --> 42:53.005
which--that went
to my fake address.

42:53.089 --> 42:55.673
And Jerry brought it to me,
and I told him

42:55.756 --> 42:58.756
I'll deposit the check,
and then he said,

42:58.839 --> 43:01.506
"You didn't get
any cash off of it?"

43:01.589 --> 43:04.214
I'm like, "No,
they gotta put a hold on it."

43:04.297 --> 43:07.047
During that time,
my bank account was always low,

43:07.130 --> 43:09.673
so I had to go back to the bank

43:09.756 --> 43:12.005
and insist on
getting something.

43:15.005 --> 43:19.089
So I got $2,000
and I gave it to him.

43:19.172 --> 43:22.297
When it did clear,
he was calling me to add

43:22.381 --> 43:24.631
to the 2,000 and make it 25.

43:25.589 --> 43:30.464
So I just took the money
and gave it to him.

43:31.506 --> 43:33.673
Didn't ask any questions.

43:33.756 --> 43:36.798
He worked out a deal where

43:36.881 --> 43:40.005
what I had, he took and, um,

43:40.089 --> 43:45.297
for the first five years,
I had to give them...

43:45.381 --> 43:49.839
give Jerry Colombo $25,000.

43:54.714 --> 43:56.130
Nothing changed for me.

43:56.214 --> 43:58.881
Now, I never acted
like I had money.

44:00.673 --> 44:04.047
'Cause I was in a deeper hole
than I was before I did it.

44:04.130 --> 44:06.255
Took my mortgage
up higher, of course.

44:06.339 --> 44:09.422
I went from paying
300 and something a month

44:09.506 --> 44:11.005
to $1,000,

44:11.089 --> 44:12.798
so I was just like--
"Phew!"

44:12.881 --> 44:15.547
That's when I found out
about the taxes.

44:16.339 --> 44:21.381
Jerry Colombo got $25,000
each time before taxes.

44:28.214 --> 44:30.381
I didn't go out
and buy anything.

44:30.464 --> 44:32.964
I couldn't buy anything.

44:33.047 --> 44:34.798
I was so stressed.

44:34.881 --> 44:37.714
Well, Jerry Colombo
always had to consult

44:37.798 --> 44:41.130
with the head man.
"Let me call Uncle Jerry."

44:41.214 --> 44:46.506
Uncle Jerry is being
reported to about everything.

44:46.589 --> 44:49.089
During that time,
I felt like Uncle Jerry

44:49.172 --> 44:52.673
was the main mob man.
[chuckles]

44:53.464 --> 44:57.130
Within that first year,
McDonald's wanted me to do

44:57.214 --> 44:58.381
all this publicity.

44:58.464 --> 45:00.464
But I just couldn't
get into it.

45:01.547 --> 45:05.881
Jerry Colombo's thing was,
"They want you to advertise

45:05.964 --> 45:09.547
"because you
are the first black,

45:09.631 --> 45:11.923
"and you're female.

45:12.005 --> 45:13.631
And you got the $1 million."

45:14.756 --> 45:18.214
And I'm saying to myself,
"Yeah, but...

45:18.297 --> 45:20.297
"I don't wanna
keep talking to people

45:20.381 --> 45:22.047
"and telling people this story

45:22.130 --> 45:24.756
over and over and over
and over and over."

45:24.839 --> 45:27.673
But he said that
we had to do this.

45:28.673 --> 45:30.214
We stayed in the Four Seasons.

45:30.297 --> 45:32.047
I think that was
the first time I ever had

45:32.130 --> 45:34.255
the opportunity to just order
what I want off the menu

45:34.339 --> 45:35.964
and not worry about a tab.

45:36.047 --> 45:38.130
Then I came in here
and the girl took so long

45:38.214 --> 45:40.631
to come out and I said,
"This must be real."

45:40.714 --> 45:44.631
So, you know, it's just--it's
just all beginning to set in.

45:44.714 --> 45:47.089
Just--I just don't know
how to describe it.

45:47.172 --> 45:49.047
It's undescribable.

45:49.130 --> 45:52.172
The best part about it,
the whole thing,

45:52.255 --> 45:55.589
is that I got a chance
to meet Sherman Hemsley.

46:00.506 --> 46:02.839
The marketing company,
they had a big celebration.

46:02.923 --> 46:04.756
It was something like
a promotion type thing

46:04.839 --> 46:06.172
and Jerry Colombo said,

46:06.255 --> 46:08.964
"Uncle Jerry's
gonna be in the audience."

46:09.047 --> 46:12.130
And I'm like, "God..."
[inhales]

46:12.214 --> 46:14.047
So...

46:14.130 --> 46:16.881
they had this big check
for me to hold

46:16.964 --> 46:20.881
and take a picture
and then they say, "Speak!"

46:20.964 --> 46:22.673
I'm like...
[sighs]

46:22.756 --> 46:24.089
Here I go.

46:24.172 --> 46:26.506
More lies.

46:28.714 --> 46:30.422
I was kind of out of it.

46:30.506 --> 46:32.255
I could hear
the cameras going.

46:32.339 --> 46:34.422
The whole time I'm thinking
about this mob man

46:34.506 --> 46:36.339
in the audience.

46:36.422 --> 46:38.798
Never seen a picture of him,

46:38.881 --> 46:41.673
didn't know
who I was looking for,

46:41.756 --> 46:46.673
but I kept looking to see
which one it could be.

46:46.756 --> 46:49.130
After that,
I finally just told him,

46:49.214 --> 46:51.464
"I don't want to
do anything else.

46:52.422 --> 46:56.714
Don't--don't put me out
to do anything else."

46:56.798 --> 47:00.798
Jerry Colombo said,
"Uncle Jerry was in the crowd.

47:00.881 --> 47:03.339
He said you did great."

47:06.589 --> 47:10.339
It just was little things
like that, that made sure,

47:10.422 --> 47:11.881
I guess, I stayed on my toes

47:11.964 --> 47:13.964
and did what I needed to do
and do it proper.

47:14.047 --> 47:19.339
So I was still under
that web the whole time.

47:19.422 --> 47:22.964
I didn't know where to turn.
I didn't know what to do.

47:23.047 --> 47:25.631
There's just really
no way out of it.

47:27.214 --> 47:30.047
And I said to myself,
"Now what's next?"

47:38.547 --> 47:42.130
- As soon as I got
that check, things changed.

47:46.589 --> 47:50.589
I'm in his car,
and we're going to this bank.

47:52.589 --> 47:56.172
We needed to get the check
cashed right there.

47:57.005 --> 48:00.547
And all the money went
right to Jerry's hands.

48:01.422 --> 48:05.047
The teller said to me,
he said, "Get that money.

48:05.130 --> 48:08.464
It's $50,000 taxes on that.

48:08.547 --> 48:10.255
Make sure you get that."

48:10.339 --> 48:12.756
But I didn't think
anything of it.

48:12.839 --> 48:15.172
It just kind of--
you go numb, you know,

48:15.255 --> 48:16.631
there's just no thought.

48:16.714 --> 48:19.631
And that's kind of how I felt,
I think,

48:19.714 --> 48:22.172
with that money,
'cause it's not mine.

48:23.464 --> 48:25.964
He said that he had
to go to Uncle Jerry first,

48:26.047 --> 48:27.589
give him his piece of pie

48:27.673 --> 48:29.631
and then everybody
gets a piece of pie

48:29.714 --> 48:31.673
and it has to go, you know,

48:31.756 --> 48:36.047
in that order
before I can get my money.

48:36.130 --> 48:39.673
So I--I kept calling him and
calling him and he would like

48:39.756 --> 48:42.047
call me back and say, "I'm
gonna get the money for you,

48:42.130 --> 48:43.673
"I got the money on me,

48:43.756 --> 48:46.130
it's gonna be like
another week," or whatever,

48:46.214 --> 48:47.673
he just kept putting me off.

48:47.756 --> 48:51.631
I heard the difference
in his voice, like, like--

48:51.714 --> 48:55.089
like, "Don't bug me.
You're gonna get your money."

48:55.172 --> 48:58.089
I--I believed...

48:58.172 --> 49:01.798
that Gennaro
owed Uncle Jerry money.

49:03.255 --> 49:07.756
I believe the money got too big

49:07.839 --> 49:12.005
to not take a bigger piece
of that pie.

49:12.089 --> 49:17.005
Because the spending habits
became bigger and grander.

49:17.089 --> 49:20.297
And I'm thinking, "Okay,

49:20.381 --> 49:22.839
that's why
I'm not getting my money."

49:25.422 --> 49:28.297
- I'm wondering if the local
banks will have the money...

